jobs_results.title: iOS Developer
jobs_results.description:
Company Description

Continental Technology Solutions is Our consulting and managed services deliver the resources and capabilities required to assess,design, build and manage an agile, flexible IT environment. You'll work with one dedicated team from strategy and assessment through design, implementation, management and optimization to reach a true end-to-end solution.

Job Description

Position: iOS Software Developer to join our Professional Services Department

Job Description:
• Work closely with the project manager and client to develop requirements, integrate internal WebRTC SDK's and libraries into production iOS applications and APIs
• Troubleshoot existing WebRTC applications and work with the internal product team to leverage internal SDK's in client applications
• Design and deliver RTC solutions in-scope, on-time, and on-budget.

We work hard, but we love what we do and have fun doing it!

Must-Have Qualifications:
• Must be able to legally work in Canada and be able to work in our office in Surrey, BC
• Bachelor’s Degree in Computing Science or equivalent
• Minimum 3 years programming experience in iOS applications - Swift and/or ObjectiveC
• Extensive experience with APNS (Apple Push Notification Service) and full development stack
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills for technical applications
• Ability to adapt and learn new technologies quickly

Additional Skills We Look For:
• Experience in WebRTC (Real Time Communications) programming
• Development experience with C#/.NET, Java, JavaScript, Android, or Xamarin
• Self motivated, can work independently, good at problem solving

Additional Information

All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.

jobs_results.title: Ios Developer
jobs_results.description:
There’s a reason you carry an iPhone in your pocket. It’s something about the iPhone look... the iPhone feel… the way your Apple Watch starts sending you heart rate alerts when your Xcode successfully compiles… or the limitless possibilities of SwiftUI, especially now that those medieval iPhone 6’s have been taken off life support.

As Transit’s newest iOS developer, you’ll be the swift-handed hero of millions of iPhone-wielders who don’t rely on a car to get around. You’ll help our team experiment, simplify, and perfect every aspect of the car-free commute: from our bodacious biking and subway maps, crowdsourced real-time displays, a devilishly simple step-by-step navigator, multimodal trip planner, and secret upcoming features you’ll discover once you’re hired.

Transit is written in Objective-C and Swift, and the business logic is implemented in a C++ shared library – our iOS and Android teams work in tandem on that part of the codebase. The shared library allows us to reduce code duplication, while maintaining high standards by using UIKit and SwiftUI on iOS to build a UI that is familiar, native, and as smooth as Steve Jobs’ forehead.

Responsibilities

Collaborate with all-star teammates to dream up Transit’s next big feature.

Develop those features, refine existing ones, and maintain the iOS app with your tender love and care.

Refactor and refine Transit’s architecture to make maintenance simpler to carry out, and new features more-easily integrated.

Conspire with our design team priests to bring their vision (and yours) to pixel-plated perfection.

✅ Requirements

You're a self starter, adaptable and detail oriented.

Good knowledge of Swift or Objective-C, plus UIKit or SwiftUI

jobs_results.title: iOS Developer (Contract)
jobs_results.description:
Intelliware is looking for iOS developers to join our team!

At Intelliware you'll have the opportunity to be part of a top-notch team and work on a wide range of consumer and enterprise mobile applications. We have virtual collaborative project rooms where you'll work closely with a cross functional team including client subject matter experts, end users, and IT teams to deliver anything from proof-of-concept prototypes to bulletproof, long living, high volume production applications.

The nature of our client project-based work allows teams the opportunity to work with a wide variety of technologies. We develop and deliver native iOS, native Android, and responsive web apps as well as consumer facing and enterprise large-scale applications. We're looking for mobile specialists to join our team and provide their expertise!

While working with a team in an agile environment, you will be:
• Developing creative, innovative and practical mobile solutions
• Estimating, tasking and prototyping
• Contributing clear and maintainable code to a shared codebase
• Collaborating with cross-functional team members on features, design and implementation
• Investigating, learning and applying new technologies/processes
• Clarifying requirements with team and client representatives

'Must Have' Skills/Experience:
• Experience developing and releasing native mobile applications
• Experience working with iOS, Swift, Xcode, and other mobile tech and IDEs
• Knowledgeable and interested in User Experience best practices and design
• Solid understanding of the full mobile development life cycle through to CI/CD
• Strong communication skills

'Nice to Have' Skills/Experience:
• Exposure to and enthusiasm for Agile approaches to software development e.g. testing, continuous integration, project rooms, pair programming, etc.
• Experience developing and releasing a mobile application with React Native
• Fluent and current in HTML5, CSS and JavaScript
• Experience with Social Network APIs such as Google APIs, Facebook and Twitter
• Experience with distributed version control
• Experience releasing to Google Play Console or iTunes App Store

For more info on Intelliware, check out our Careers Page and Instagram.

Intelliware is committed to diversity in the workplace. We are an inclusive employer and welcome and encourage applications from all qualified candidates. Applicants' needs will be accommodated during our recruitment and selection process so please advise us if you require accommodation.

jobs_results.title: Mobile Application Developer (Android & iOS)
jobs_results.description:
Our client has engaged ROSS (www.getROSS.com) to find a phenomenal Mobile Application Developer (Android & iOS) for an amazing permanent opportunity in downtown Toronto.

Our Agency:

ROSS is an innovative leader in Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), HR Technology, Recruitment and HR Professional Services. We’re a company of People Specialists helping companies align their People Strategy with their Business Growth.

Our Client:

This is a client like no other. Not only are they 100% Canadian owned, they have earned a leading place in Canada’s payment processing industry. Our client provides secure electronic payment processing services, including INTERAC Online, credit card processing and cutting-edge secure mobile commerce.

The Opportunity:

Our client is expanding and looking for an experienced Mobile Application Developer (Android / iOS) to join their stellar team.

The iOS/Android Mobile Application Developer handles development using Java, Objective-C, and various open source frameworks and technologies. Responsibilities include design, development, and implementation of large and small scale mobile projects using Agile methodologies for a variety of our clients. You will lead large and small development efforts for various mobile product efforts and customer projects. This position will have responsibility for designing and developing features and implementing cutting edge solutions using technologies and frameworks such as: Android, Cocoa Touch, HTML5 / JavaScript, Flex, AIR, Objective-C, Java, Design Patterns, XML, JSON, SQLITE.

Responsibilities:
• Work with internal development team to design and develop code, test and document native applications on iOS and Android platforms
• Develop, enhance, maintain, document, and otherwise support mobile applications using cases, business process flows, UI design, and UML modeling, following prescribed standards and development methodologies
• Work with internal ad hoc product development team to design, code, test, and document new features and applications; work with other developers to develop functionality following existing style and coding standards
• Interact with customers and prospects to review designs, demo prototypes and address issues.
• Provide technical support to internal clients
• Understand system architecture with an eye to scalability and efficiency
• Ensure development projects are delivered on schedule, on budget, and to specification
• Participate in ad-hoc projects and assignments as required

Qualifications:
• Bachelor of Science in Computer Science or related field
• Minimum of 2-3 years experience developing enterprise or client facing applications for mobile devices, including hands-on experience with both native and mobile web applications on iPhone/iPad, Android, Blackberry SDK, Windows Phone; experience with mobile device management, application deployment and support strongly desired
• Hands on development experience with rich user interface technologies for mobile. Implementation experience of software design patterns and best practices applicable to mobile development.
Deep working knowledge of the general mobile landscape, architectures, trends, and emerging technologies
• Experience with client side application scripting, e.g., JavaScript
• Experience with Java including Java/J2ME, Objective-C, HTML, XML, CSS, web services and databases
• Experience with version control systems such as Subversion; comfort with OOP coding principles
• Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to think logically
• Familiarity with software development methodologies and testing best practices
• Good written and verbal communication skills
• Excellent teamwork skills, flexibility, and ability to handle multiple tasks
• Able to manage one's own time efficiently
• Experience with quality control and usability, and version control
• Must be proactive, self-directed, organised , detail oriented and a quick learner
• Experience with project management
• Experience with Scrum process an asset
• A passion for mobile applications
• Must be willing and able to work in the US for a period of roughly 4 to 6 weeks duration.

Referral Bonus:
If you're not interested, but know someone who is, please help a current or former colleague in their career development by referring them. In addition, we're happy to give you a $1,000 referral fee. Click http://www.getROSS.com/referral_fee.php for more details.

jobs_results.description:

As an iOS Developer and part of our team, you will be responsible for creating iOS code mainly in Swift. Understanding of other languages like Objective-C are also useful. Push is a leader in custom mobile app development for iPhone and Android across a broad range of industries.
The work for this job is in person at our Saskatoon office. Relocation may be required before starting work.
You must have the ability to legally work in Canada.
Responsibilities:
Your job will be to deliver high-quality iOS code for our mobile applications for clients. You will in time also be looked upon to assist in other tasks such as mentoring other developers, assisting in planning and estimating projects, contributing ideas to improve our processes, and helping drive the team to hit deadlines – all while helping to deliver quality applications to our clients. You will have the opportunity to contribute to many different projects that will challenge you and help hone your skills.
Typical daily tasks may include:
Creating a new or updating an existing iOS Application code
Developing new features
Performing code reviews
Helping demo a new build to a client
Helping another developer solve a problem
Required Skills:
• 1+ years of iOS development experience
• 2 years of software development experience
• Strong understanding of Swift
• Drive to build and maintain quality software that is mission critical to our clients.
• Ability to collaborate with a multi-disciplinary team
• Initiative to deliver working software quickly and effectively
• Enthusiasm to work in an iterative agile development process
• Ability to think about long term maintenance when creating or maintaining software
• Experience with Git

• Experience consuming web services, including caching for offline usage

Education:
~ Bachelor's Degree or higher (preferred)
